wiki.content: Jisoo’s “Earthquake” is an electrifying depiction of overwhelming attraction, using the metaphor of an earthquake to convey the intensity of emotions. The lyrics describe the all-consuming nature of desire, with the narrator feeling their heart race uncontrollably and their body trembling, emphasizing the physical and emotional impact of this connection. The song captures the paradox of wanting to escape yet being unable to resist. The pre-chorus builds tension, warning of an impending shock, while the chorus delivers an explosive release, mirroring the unpredictability of an actual earthquake. The bridge deepens the sense of surrender, as the narrator embraces their emotions despite knowing they are falling. With its pulsating beat, high-energy repetition, and hypnotic structure, “Earthquake” paints love as a force of nature—inescapable, all-consuming, and exhilarating. Read more on Last.fm.
